---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../components/SiteHeader.astro';
import { siteConfig } from '../config/site';
---

<Layout
	title={`About ${siteConfig.name} | AI, Autonomous Governance & Sustainable Food Production`}
	description={`${siteConfig.name} develops AI-based autonomous governance systems for sustainable food production. Our flagship product, ${siteConfig.name} GaiaOS, combines multi-agent architecture, Digital Twin and edge computing for proactive governance of agricultural environments.`}
>
	<a class="skip-link" href="#main-content">Skip to content</a>

	<div class="page">
		<SiteHeader />

		<main id="main-content">
			<section class="hero">
				<p class="eyebrow">About</p>
				<div class="hero-layout">
					<div class="hero-copy">
						<h1 class="display-title">The future of sustainable production will not be monitored. It will be governed.</h1>
						<p class="hero-text">
							Leaftix develops AI-based autonomous governance systems for sustainable food
							production. Our flagship product, Leaftix GaiaOS, combines multi-agent
							architecture, Digital Twin and edge computing for proactive governance of
							agricultural environments — from monitoring to autonomous decision-making.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="hero-logo-wrap">
						<img
							class="hero-logo"
							src="/leaftix-logo.png"
							alt="Leaftix Logo — Green leaf symbol representing sustainable agriculture technology"
							width="320"
							height="416"
							loading="eager"
							decoding="async"
						/>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="editorial-section">
				<div class="section-rail">
					<p class="section-kicker">Our Mission</p>
				</div>
				<div class="story-block">
					<p>
						A manifesto for planetary resilience, driven by artificial intelligence and
						absolute data precision. Leaftix was built on the conviction that the future
						of sustainable production will not be monitored — it will be governed by
						autonomous intelligence.
					</p>
					<p>
						We believe that the complexity of climate risk demands a new kind of
						infrastructure: one that connects environmental sensors, edge nodes and
						autonomous machinery into a single, cohesive intelligence capable of
						anticipating and mitigating threats before they impact production.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="editorial-section">
				<div class="section-rail">
					<p class="section-kicker">What is Leaftix GaiaOS?</p>
				</div>
				<div class="story-block">
					<p>
						Leaftix GaiaOS is not just a control panel. It is the underlying logical
						layer connecting environmental sensors, edge nodes and autonomous machinery
						into a single, cohesive intelligence, capable of anticipating and mitigating
						climate risk before it impacts production.
					</p>
					<p>
						It is a multi-agent cognitive infrastructure that ingests terabytes of
						environmental data in real time — including climate patterns, soil moisture,
						temperature gradients, market data and IoT sensor inputs — feeding a
						hierarchical AI system that enables proactive governance at every level.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="editorial-section">
				<div class="section-rail">
					<p class="section-kicker">Architecture</p>
				</div>
				<div class="story-block">
					<p>
						Leaftix GaiaOS uses a tripartite mythological architecture. The Olympus layer
						acts as the sovereignty council with Gaia (the Supreme Orchestrator), Athena
						(the Surveillance Strategist) and Hermes (the Capital Strategist) — resolving
						conflicts, routing tasks and maintaining strategic vision. Terra is the
						manifestation interface and physical execution layer. Hades is the material
						intelligence engine, responsible for deep data mining and pattern discovery.
					</p>
					<p>
						This structure ensures robust hierarchical and multi-agent governance,
						delivering proven results: a 34% reduction in energy consumption per gram of
						biomass and a Digital Twin variance under 2%, setting a new standard for
						precision in agricultural intelligence.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>
		</main>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style>
	.page {
		position: relative;
		width: min(calc(100% - 3rem), 78rem);
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 1.25rem 0 5rem;
	}

	.eyebrow,
	.section-kicker {
		font-family: var(--font-mono);
		font-size: 0.82rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: 0.08em;
		line-height: 1.4;
		text-transform: uppercase;
	}

	.hero {
		padding: 6rem 0 4rem;
	}

	.hero-layout {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.35fr) minmax(15rem, 20rem);
		gap: 2.5rem;
		align-items: start;
		margin-top: 1rem;
	}

	.hero-copy {
		max-width: 52rem;
	}

	.eyebrow,
	.section-kicker {
		margin: 0;
		color: var(--muted-foreground);
		font-style: normal;
	}

	.hero-text,
	.story-block p {
		font-size: 1.08rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.hero-text {
		max-width: 44rem;
		margin-top: 1.5rem;
	}

	.hero-logo-wrap {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: flex-end;
		align-self: start;
		padding-top: 0.35rem;
	}

	.hero-logo {
		width: min(100%, 16rem);
		height: auto;
		display: block;
	}

	.editorial-section {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 16rem minmax(0, 1fr);
		gap: 2rem;
		padding: 2.5rem 0;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
	}

	.section-rail {
		align-self: start;
	}

	.story-block {
		display: grid;
		gap: 1rem;
		max-width: 52rem;
	}

	@media (max-width: 1100px) {
		.hero-layout {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			gap: 1.75rem;
			align-items: start;
		}

		.hero-copy {
			max-width: 100%;
		}

		.hero-text {
			max-width: 42rem;
		}

		.hero-logo-wrap {
			justify-content: flex-start;
			padding-top: 0;
		}
	}

	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.page {
			width: min(calc(100% - 1.5rem), 78rem);
			padding-top: 1rem;
		}

		.hero {
			padding: 4rem 0 3rem;
		}

		.editorial-section {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.hero-text,
		.story-block p {
			font-size: 1.05rem;
		}

		.hero-logo {
			width: min(100%, 12rem);
		}
	}
</style>